AN ACT relating to education; establishing the Commission on
Racial Equity and Social Justice; prescribing the
membership and duties of the Commission; requiring the
Board of Regents of the University of Nevada to provide
certain support to the Commission; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Article 11 of the Nevada Constitution requires the Nevada Legislature to
2 provide for the establishment of a State University that is controlled by a Board of
3 Regents whose duties are prescribed by law. (Nev. Const. Art. 11, § 4) Existing law
4 establishes the Nevada System of Higher Education, which consists of the State
5 University and certain other educational institutions, programs and operations.
6 (NRS 396.020)
7 This bill creates the Commission on Racial Equity and Social Justice for the
8 purposes of studying issues and making recommendations to the 84th Session of
9 the Nevada Legislature relating to certain matters of racial discrimination in this
10 State. Section 2 of this bill creates the Commission and prescribes the membership
11 of the Commission, consisting of nine members appointed on or before August 1,
12 2025, as follows: (1) three members appointed by the President of the University of
13 Nevada, Las Vegas; (2) three members appointed by the President of the University
14 of Nevada, Reno; (3) one member appointed by the Governor; (4) one member
15 appointed by the Senate Majority Leader; and (5) one member appointed by the
16 Speaker of the Assembly.
17 Section 2 of this bill establishes the duties of the Commission and, among other
18 duties, requires the Commission to: (1) study certain matters relating to historical
19 discrimination in this State and the related economic effects of the discrimination to
20 present day society in this State; and (2) make recommendations relating to its
21 findings to the 84th Session of the Nevada Legislature for methods to educate the
22 general public about the findings and recommendations of the Commission,
