THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Commission on Racial Equity and Social
2 Justice is hereby created for the purposes of studying issues and
3 making recommendations to the 84th Session of the Nevada
4 Legislature relating to racial discrimination in this State.
5 2. The Commission consists of the following nine members:
6 (a) Three members appointed by the President of the University
7 of Nevada, Las Vegas, or his or her designee;
8 (b) Three members appointed by the President of the University
9 of Nevada, Reno, or his or her designee;
10 (c) One member appointed by the Governor;
11 (d) One member appointed by the Senate Majority Leader; and
12 (e) One member appointed by the Speaker of the Assembly.
13  In making appointments to the Commission, the appointing
14 authorities shall appoint members of the Commission on the basis of
15 their education, training and experience in the fields of African
16 American studies and reparatory justice. The appointing authorities
17 shall appoint members of the Commission on or before August 1,
18 2025.
19 3. An elected official of any governmental entity is not eligible
20 to be appointed to the Commission.
21 4. Any vacancy occurring in the membership of the
22 Commission shall not affect the powers and duties of the
23 Commission and shall be filled in the same manner as the original
24 appointment.
25 5. The compensation each member of the Commission is
26 entitled to receive, if any, shall be established by the Board of
27 Regents.
28 6. The President of the University of Nevada, Las Vegas, and
29 the President of the University of Nevada, Reno, shall jointly
