1 appoint a Chair and Vice Chair of the Commission, who serve in
2 such positions until the Commission expires by limitation.
3 7. The Commission shall:
4 (a) Hold its first meeting not later than 30 days after all the
5 appointments are made pursuant to subsection 2;
6 (b) Meet as a whole at least four times before the Commission
7 expires by limitation and may meet at such further times and places
8 specified by a call of the Chair.
9 8. The Chair of the Commission may establish subcommittees
10 to assist the Commission in the performance of its duties. The
11 subcommittees shall meet at the times and places specified by a call
12 of the Chair.
13 Sec. 2. 1. The Commission shall study:
14 (a) The economic, political, social, educational and historical
15 impacts of slavery, Jim Crow laws, de jure and de facto racial
16 segregation and other forms of racial discrimination in the State of
17 Nevada, as well as the prior organized and unorganized territories
18 that constitute a part of the current state boundaries of the State;
19 (b) Discriminatory habits or practices, including, without
20 limitation, forced slavery, chattel slavery, indentured servitude,
21 redlining, segregated school systems and segregated public goods
22 and spaces, that may have caused significant economic or societal
23 disparities of formerly enslaved Africans or their descendants; and
24 (c) The related economic effects to present day society in the
25 State of Nevada as a result of the matters studied pursuant to this
26 subsection.
27 2. The Commission shall present its findings and make
28 recommendations relating to its findings to the 84th Session of the
29 Nevada Legislature for:
30 (a) Methods to educate the general public of the State of Nevada
31 of the Commission’s findings and recommendations;
32 (b) Advancement of racial healing, understanding and
33 transformation;
34 (c) Forms of rehabilitation or restitution to the descendants of
35 formerly enslaved Africans, if warranted, based on the findings
36 of the Commission. If the Commission finds that any form of
37 rehabilitation or restitution is warranted, then the form and scope of
38 such measures.
39 3. The Commission may collaborate and consult with and
40 invite participation by historians, scholars and any other interested
41 parties.
42 4. Each state agency, as defined in NRS 277.186, shall
43 cooperate with the Commission and timely provide any information
44 that may be requested by the Commission relating to its duties.
