6 Sec. 3. 1. The Board of Regents shall provide administrative
7 support to the Commission, including, without limitation, providing
8 meeting spaces, technical assistance, organizational support,
9 assistance with public communications and media relations and any
10 other necessary tasks required by the Commission in the furtherance
11 of its duties. The Board of Regents must be prepared to provide such
12 support not later than August 1, 2025.
13 2. The Board of Regents may accept gifts, grants and donations
14 to fund the Commission in carrying out its duties.
15 Sec. 4. 1. On or before January 31, 2027, the Commission on
16 Racial Equity and Social Justice created by section 2 of this act shall
17 prepare and submit a report to the Director of the Legislative
18 Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the 84th Session of the Nevada
19 Legislature on the work of the Commission relating to the duties of
20 the Commission set forth in section 2 of this act.
21 2. On or before the adjournment of the 84th Legislative
22 Session sine die, the Commission shall present in person its findings
23 and recommendations to the Legislature.
24 Sec. 5. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
